@startuml
left to right direction

actor "Job Seeker" as User
actor "File System" as FS

rectangle "Job Application Tracker" {

  usecase "Add Job Application" as UC1
  usecase "Update Application Status" as UC2
  usecase "View Applications" as UC3
  usecase "Delete Application" as UC4
  usecase "Search Applications" as UC5

  User --> UC1
  User --> UC2
  User --> UC3
  User --> UC4
  User --> UC5

  UC1 --> FS
  UC2 --> FS
  UC3 --> FS
  UC4 --> FS
  UC5 --> FS
}

note right of User
The Job Seeker is the primary actor who interacts with the Job
Application Tracker to manage personal job applications. The user
adds, updates, views, searches, and deletes applications while
tracking the job search process.
end note

note right of FS
The File System is a secondary actor that provides persistent
storage for job application data. It supports saving and retrieving
information used by the system.
end note

note bottom of UC1
This use case allows the user to enter job details such as company
name, job title, and application date. The system validates and
stores the information.
end note

note bottom of UC2
This use case enables the user to update the current status of a job
application, such as Applied, Interviewing, Offered, or Rejected.
end note

note bottom of UC3
This use case allows the user to view all job applications and their
associated details in the system.
end note

note bottom of UC4
This use case allows the user to remove a job application that is no
longer relevant from the tracker.
end note

note bottom of UC5
This use case enables the user to search job applications using
criteria such as company name or status.
end note

@enduml
